ollution. Although there are no specific figures for China, it is reasonable to infer that China, as a large developing country, bears a significant proportion of such deaths.\\n\\nIn conclusion, pollution, especially air pollution, poses a significant threat to human health in China, resulting in a large number of premature deaths. However, China has taken a series of measures to control pollution in recent years, and the situation is gradually improving.\"}","event_id":"68","event_type":2001}

